body:
### Code

```Rust
fn test<T: Trait>(a: &[T]){}

trait Trait {}
struct Concrete(i32);

impl Trait for Concrete {}

fn main(){
    let a = &Concrete(5);
    test(&[a]);
}
```


### Current output

```Shell
...
help: consider removing the leading `&`-reference
   |
10 -     test(&[a]);
10 +     test([a]);
   |
```


### Desired output

```Shell
...
help: consider removing the leading `&`-reference
   |
9  -     let a = &Concrete(5);
9  +     let a = Concrete(5);
   |
```


### Rationale and extra context

the suggested help message, when applied, will cause another issue: "expected reference found array" as it changes the argument from a slice to a array

### Other cases

_No response_

### Anything else?

Issue exists in Release 1.69.0 and Nightly 1.71.0-nightly 2023-05-16 e77366b57b799dfa3ce1

